edu.uta.cse.fireeye.service.engine

Class CoverageChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uta.cse.fireeye.service.engine.CoverageChecker

  • public class CoverageChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    This class checks if a test set satisfies t-way coverage. Note that it uses an AETG-like algorithm to maintain independence from the algorithm used for test generation.

      • check

        public boolean check()
        Checks whether the test set satisfies t-way coverage. This method considers the possible existence of constraints and relations. So, the coverage it checks may not be a simple t-way coverage.
        Returns:
        true if t-way coverage is satisfied.
